id: pm-github-q3lk
title: Export --apply aborts the whole batch on the first failed item
description: "The exporter's --apply loop did 'await request(...)' per item with no try/catch. A single failed create/update (e.g. a 422 for a label that does not exist on the repo) threw and abandoned every remaining item, with no record of what was already written. The import/sync paths already isolate per-item failures (skipped++/continue); the export path did not."
type: Issue
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags: []
created_at: "2026-06-05T14:47:06.754Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-05T14:47:13.857Z"
author: codex
acceptance_criteria: per-item apply failures isolated and counted; batch completes with a summary; happy path + dry-run byte-identical; unit test proves continue-on-failure
